===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{synonym of|en|lazaretto}}
## {{lb|en|historical}} A [[place#Noun|place]] [[reserve#Verb|reserved]] for [[person#Noun|people]] with [[infectious disease]]s (especially those with [[leprosy]] or [[plague#Noun|plague]]) to [[live#Verb|live]] on a [[long-term]] [[basis]].
##* '''1938''', [[w:Xavier Herbert|Xavier Herbert]], ''[[w:Capricornia (novel)|Capricornia]]'', New York: D. Appleton-Century, 1943, Chapter II, p. 10, [https://archive.org/details/capricornianovel00herb]
##*: But the civilising was so complete that the survivors of the original inhabitants numbered seven, of whom two were dying of consumption in the Native Compound, three confined in the Native '''Lazaret''' with leprosy, the rest, a man and a woman, living in a gunyah at the remote end of Devilfish Bay, subsisting on what food they could get from the bush and the sea and what they could buy with the pennies the man earned by doing odd jobs and the woman by prostitution.
##* '''1989''', Richard Winston & al. translating [[w:Carl Jung|Carl Jung]] & al. as ''Memories, Dreams, Reflections'', p. 108:
##*: The director was locked up in the same institution with his patients, and the institution was equally cut off, isolated on the outskirts of the city like an ancient '''lazaret''' with its lepers.
## {{lb|en|historical|also|figuratively}} A [[building#Noub|building]] such as a [[hospital]], or occasionally a [[ship#Noun|ship]], [[use#Verb|used]] to [[isolate#Verb|isolate]] [[sick#Adjective|sick]] people to [[prevent]] the [[spread#Noun|spread]] of infectious diseases; a [[quarantine#Noun|quarantine]].
##* {{RQ:Byron Don Juan|canto=II|lines=215–216|passage=The liver is the '''lazaret''' of bile, / But very rarely executes its function}}
## {{lb|en|nautical}} A place at the [[front#Preposition|front]] of the [[tweendeck]]s of a [[merchant ship]] where [[provision#Noun|provisions]] are [[store#Verb|stored]].

